sections.Trivia:
- Keinobu Kuroda (黒田 佳展, Kuroda Keinobu) is mistakenly written in the ending credits as Keinobu Kuroi (黒井 佳展, Kuroi Keinobu).
- Some of the characters' Japanese surnames have relatively regular patterns. Named after gold, wood, water, fire and earth, this is called gogyo, originated from Chinese philosophy Wuxing:
Tae Kinbara (金原 妙) represents gold (金);
Akira Kisugi (木杉 彬) represents wood (木);
Toko Mizutani (水谷 統子) represents water (水);
Keisuke Hida (火田 啓介) represents fire (火);
Katsuhiro Doigaki (土井 垣克広) represents earth (土).
